value.0: Although colorless, odorless, and tasteless, water is thirst-quenching and needed for life.  Many city-folk who do not live near a well or river must purchase water from a market.
This is a pipe carved out of wood and bone.
These are some metal utensils for eating.
This lotion, made from various plant and animal products, is applied to the skin for a smooth, pleasant-scented feel.
This kit comes with a variety of inks and brushes used for painting.
This is nothing more than a blank sheet of paper that can be written on.

Dark and sweet-scented, this Nexalan leaf can be used for the
same purposes as common pipeweed.  However, there all comparison ends, for pipeweed cannot match the rich, full flavors of true Nexalan tabacco (or tobacco).
A small, portable mirror used to see your reflection.
This is a simple mug, used to drink ale or other beverages.
This is a pot filled with ink for writing.
Simply an attractive goblet, usually used to sip wine.
This is a simple rag doll -- a toy preferred by young girls.
This is a clock that can be carried around in order to examine the time.
This is a canteen, used to carry water on long travels.
Almonds are a flavorful oval-shaped nut.
Produced from cow's milk, cheese is a delicious food that goes well with a good wine.
Assorted nuts are good sources of nutrition.
This is a standard lantern, you must refill it with oil every 6 hours of use.
This is an oil flask.  You may use it to refill a lantern, or try to light it and throw at someone
This is a standard cheap disposable torch.
This is a bedroll.  You can use it by placing it on the ground.
This is a bedroll, to use it, drop it on the ground.
These bandages may be used to provide first aid or long-term care.  They do not treat poison or disease.
This is a broom... nothing more,  nothing less.
This shovel has a metal head attached to a wooden shaft.  It is useful for digging.
This hoe is used for tilling soil.
Rangers can use tracking kits to track enemies while in the wilderness.
